First Among Us I once heard some words of reassurance:
&ldquo;My son, know that I would not do again what I have already done.&rdquo;
Voices interupt with aggressive questions
&ldquo;I wont leave my son again&rdquo;
&ldquo;They should be asking: &lsquo;What is it they can do to pay?&rdquo;
After some time I thought about his son dying for our sins and what a powerful sacrifice that was. Then, what a big debt that was to pay.
